  "27-29": (
    caption: [First elongation step in bacteria: binding of the second aminoacyl-tRNA. The second aminoacyl-tRNA (AA2) enters the A site of the ribosome bound to GTP-bound EF-Tu (shown here as Tu). Binding of the second aminoacyl-tRNA to the A site is accompanied by hydrolysis of the GTP to GDP and Pi and release of the EF-Tu–GDP complex from the ribosome. The bound GDP is released when the EF-Tu–GDP complex binds to EF-Ts, and EF-Ts is subsequently released when another molecule of GTP binds to EF-Tu. This recycles EF-Tu and makes it available to repeat the cycle. Accommodation involves a change in the second tRNA confor- mation that pulls its aminoacyl end into the peptidyl transferase site. c27ProteinMetabolism.indd Page 1132 18/10/12 11:31 AM user-F408 c27ProteinMetabolism.indd Page 1132 18/10/12 11:31 AM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 1132],
