    caption: [Second elongation step in bacteria: formation of the first peptide bond. The peptidyl transferase catalyzing this reaction is the 23S rRNA ribozyme. The N-formylmethionyl group is transferred to the amino group of the second aminoacyl-tRNA in the A site, forming a dipeptidyl- tRNA. At this stage, both tRNAs bound to the ribosome shift position in],
